        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Initial production 2002 Caterpillar Emission Engines may exhibit premature belt wear or failure.
                    If the edges of the belt are showing wear, the belt should be replaced with the new part numbers
                    listed below. If the main drive belt has not stayed on the pulleys, in addition to replacing the
                    belt with the new part number, the pulley grooves should also be cleaned with a wire brush before
                    installing the new belt. Vehicles built after the date listed below should have the new belts and
                    should not exhibit premature belt wear or failure.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
